result.description: This refers to a type of non-alcoholic beverage infused with THC (Tetrahydrocannabinol) and CBD (Cannabidiol), compounds derived from cannabis. THC is the primary psychoactive component in cannabis, while CBD is non-psychoactive and is associated with potential therapeutic effects such as alleviating anxiety and chronic pain. These beverages offer a novel way to consume cannabis, providing an alternative to traditional smoking methods.

These are drinks specifically formulated with health-promoting ingredients such as vitamins, minerals, antioxidants, and herbs. They aim to enhance overall wellness by providing nutritional benefits beyond basic hydration. Examples include green tea, kombucha, and protein shakes. The market for these beverages is growing as consumers increasingly seek healthier lifestyle choices.
